<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-402-726  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 402 726.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  July 4 1989* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CD-ROM encyclopedia for Mac. (New Electronic Encyclopedia)(product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Grolier Electronic Publishing Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Grolier Electronic Publishing New Electronic Encyclopedia(Information retrieval system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Optical MemoryCD-ROMEncyclopediasProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CD-ROM ENCYCLOPEDIA FOR MAC DANBURY, CONNECTICUT, U.S.A., 1989 JUN 20 (NB) --Grolier Electronic Publishing has announced a Macintosh version of The NewElectronic Encyclopedia.andP;  Introduced at the American Library Association'sconference in Dallas June 23-28, the encyclopedia, which ships in July andwill cost $395, is on CD-ROM disk and is comprised of 21 volumes, over 30,000articles, and more than nine million words of Grolier's Academic AmericanEncyclopedia.andM;The software exploits the Macintosh windows to stack, sort, size, or resizeentries.andP;  An electronic bookmark saves the user's place for quick access andreference at a later time.andP;  The disk is in High Sierra format.andP;  The same diskwill also run on MS-DOS machines, demonstrating the technical achievement ofOnline Computer Systems of Germantown, Maryland.andP;  Online developed theproduct's search and retrieval software.andM;(Wendy Woods/19890701/Press Contact: Adriene O'Brien, Grolier, 800-356-5590or 203-797-3359)</TEXT></DOC>